FBIS3-57843 "drweu002_o_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-002 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Jan 1994 CYPRUS UNFICYP Spokesman Comments NC0401081094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 0530 GMT 4 Jan 94 NC0401081094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] The Turkish side made new allegations yesterday by claiming that there were incidents on the confrontation line. In an Istanbul dispatch, ANATOLIA News Agency reported that the Rauf Denktas regime reported to the UN Forces in Cyprus [UNFICYP] that the Turkish positions were fired upon by Greek Cypriots. According to the news agency, the so-called incident took place at noon yesterday. A UNFICYP spokesman to CyBC [Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation] said last night that he has no information about the Turkish allegations. At the same time, the National Guard General Staff stressed that the Turkish allegations are a new attempt to create problems.
